{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"eae91ab4-5171-4807-9296-f5ff05774a20","content":"Here's how to migrate:\n\n### 1. Replace `VSTest@3` with `DotNetCoreCLI@2` (or a plain `dotnet test` script)\n\nMicrosoft.Testing.Platform doesn't use `vstest.console.exe`, so `VSTest@3` won't work. Use `dotnet test` instead:\n\n```yaml\n- task: DotNetCoreCLI@2\n  displayName: 'Run tests'\n  inputs:\n    command: test\n    projects: '**/*.Tests.csproj'\n    arguments: >\n      --configuration Release\n      --logger \"trx;LogFileName=results.trx\"\n      --results-directory $(Agent.TempDirectory)/TestResults\n      --collect \"Code Coverage;Format=Cobertura\"\n```\n\n### 2. Publish TRX results\n\n```yaml\n- task: PublishTestResults@2\n  displayName: 'Publish test results'\n  condition: always()\n  inputs:\n    testResultsFormat: VSTest\n    testResultsFiles: '$(Agent.TempDirectory)/TestResults/**/*.trx'\n```\n\n### 3. Publish code coverage\n\n```yaml\n- task: PublishCodeCoverageResults@2\n  displayName: 'Publish code coverage'\n  condition: always()\n  inputs:\n    summaryFileLocation: '$(Agent.TempDirectory)/TestResults/**/coverage.cobertura.xml'\n```\n\n### Key differences from VSTest@3\n\n| Concern | Before (VSTest@3) | After |\n|---|---|---|\n| Test runner | `vstest.console.exe` | `dotnet test` (in-process) |\n| TRX reports | Built-in | `--logger trx` |\n| Code coverage | Built-in collector | `--collect \"Code Coverage\"` |\n| Result publish | Automatic | Separate `PublishTestResults@2` task |\n\n### Project-side prerequisite\n\nEnsure your test projects opt in to the new platform in their `.csproj`:\n\n```xml\n<PropertyGroup>\n  <EnableMSTestRunner>true</EnableMSTestRunner>\n  <OutputType>Exe</OutputType>\n</PropertyGroup>\n```\n\nThe `condition: always()` on the publish tasks ensures results are uploaded even when tests fail.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"51603836-8833-48fa-97b5-c426cbd69869","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The repository is empty. This is a general question about migrating from VSTest@3 to Microsoft.Testing.Platform in Azure DevOps pipelines. Let me provide a concise answer based on my knowledge.","outputTokens":603,"requestId":"1BDD:37D8BB:205FEC1:23C466F:6A03CE73"},"id":"9d222246-c85e-4d29-a2e9-f7dd7ac7603d","timestamp":"2026-05-13T01:06:05.648Z","parentId":"ece3c216-1c66-432f-839e-ef7359717b94"}
